    <div class="container">
        <section id="overview" class="content">
            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>Session Initiation Protocol (SIP) is a signaling protocol used for initiating, maintaining, and terminating real-time sessions that include voice, video, and messaging applications. SIP is widely used in internet telephony for voice and video calls, as well as in private IP telephone systems.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="features" class="content">
            <h2>Features</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Peer-to-Peer Connectivity: SIP allows direct connection between participants.</li>
                <li>Flexibility: SIP can be used for a variety of applications including voice, video, and instant messaging.</li>
                <li>Scalability: SIP can handle a large number of participants and connections simultaneously.</li>
                <li>Interoperability: SIP works with many different devices and applications, ensuring wide compatibility.</li>
                <li>Security: SIP supports encryption and authentication methods to ensure secure communication.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section id="applications" class="content">
            <h2>Applications</h2>
            <p>SIP is used in various applications such as:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Internet Telephony: For making voice and video calls over the internet.</li>
                <li>Unified Communications: Integrating voice, video, messaging, and data services.</li>
                <li>Instant Messaging: Enabling real-time text communication.</li>
                <li>Multimedia Distribution: Streaming audio and video content.</li>
                <li>Conferencing: Facilitating multi-party audio and video conferences.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section id="resources" class="content">
            <h2>Resources</h2>
            <p>For more information about SIP, you can visit the following resources:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3261" target="_blank">SIP RFC 3261</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.voip-info.org/sip/" target="_blank">VoIP-Info SIP Overview</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Session_Initiation_Protocol" target="_blank">Wikipedia: Session Initiation Protocol</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.sipforum.org/" target="_blank">SIP Forum</a></li>
            </ul>
        </section>
